## SEGMENT 1 — Why Claude Is Different (and Why It Matters for You) (8 minutes)

**The point you're making:** Claude isn't just another AI chatbot. It has a memory system, a reasoning depth, and a context capacity that makes it uniquely suited to running actual business workflows — not just answering questions.

---

"Most people have used ChatGPT. Some of you have played with Gemini, Copilot, a few others. So I want to explain exactly why I landed on Claude — and why I teach Claude specifically for small business owners.

Three things separate Claude from the rest.

First: context window. Claude can hold an enormous amount of information in a single conversation. That means you can paste in your client history, your offer details, your bio, your sales script — all of it — and Claude can work with all of it at once. Most tools have limits that force you to keep starting over. Claude doesn't.

Second: instruction-following. Claude is exceptionally good at following complex, layered instructions. That matters because running a business isn't a single task. It's a system of tasks. You need a tool that can handle nuance, hold multiple requirements at once, and not drift off into generic output the second you give it a real-world constraint.

Third: reasoning. When you ask Claude to write something, it's not pattern-matching the most common words associated with your topic. It's actually working through the logic of your situation. That's why Claude output — when you prompt it right — sounds like something a smart person wrote, not something a content farm generated.

Now, none of that matters if you're using it wrong. And that brings me to the single biggest mistake I see small business owners make with Claude."

