## SEGMENT 2 — The #1 Mistake (And Why People Quit) (8 minutes)

**The point you're making:** People treat Claude like a vending machine — drop in a generic question, expect a usable answer. It doesn't work that way. Claude needs context. The blank prompt produces blank results.

---

"Here's the mistake. And if you've tried Claude before and walked away disappointed, I'm almost certain this is what happened.

People open Claude and they type something like: 'Write me a social media post for my business.'

And Claude writes something. And it's generic. And it kind of sounds like every other AI post they've ever seen. And they think — this tool is overhyped.

The tool isn't overhyped. The prompt is broken.

Think of it this way. If you hired a new employee and their first day on the job, you walked up and said, 'Do some marketing,' what would you get? You'd get whatever that person decided to do based on zero information about your business, your clients, your voice, or your goals.

That's what a blank Claude prompt is. You are giving Claude a first-day employee with no onboarding and asking for expert-level output.

The fix is context. Specifically: three types of context that Claude needs before it can do real work for you.

One — who you are and what your business does. Not a paragraph. A structured brief. Your name, your offer, who you serve, what problem you solve, and what makes you different.

Two — your voice. How you talk. What you never say. The tone of your emails, your posts, your conversations. Claude will mirror this if you give it to Claude. If you don't, it will default to whatever it was trained on, which is the internet, which is not you.

Three — the specific task and context. Not just 'write a social post.' Write a social post for a business coach targeting women in corporate who are thinking about leaving their jobs — use this hook, reference this pain point, and keep the tone conversational but authoritative.

That third prompt is going to give you something you can actually post. The first one is going to give you something you'll delete.

Tonight I'm going to show you exactly how to build that context and give it to Claude. And then I'm going to do a live comparison so you can see the difference with your own eyes."

